    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-05T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/8921</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-05T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 6, 3.20 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4093. War Trade Board [from <persName>Stetson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 154. We are informed by British and French that it was decided at a meeting
                    held in Washington May 8, that I. B. C, Paris, is in certain limited cases to
                    determine the suitability of granting licenses for export from Allied countries
                    to firms and individuals on the black lists for Spain, Morocco, and Switzerland.
                    We are without any information, advice, or instructions on this point, and would
                    appreciate being informed if we are to handle this matter, so that we may, if
                    desired, cooperate with other representatives of the Associated Governments.
                        <persName>Stetson</persName>, <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
